00:11:15,809 --> 00:11:17,244
The normal rules apply,

249
00:11:17,277 --> 00:11:19,579
which means if she puts
too much distance between us,

250
00:11:19,613 --> 00:11:21,014
the magnetism should weaken.

251
00:11:21,048 --> 00:11:23,751
Avdol: So what should we do?
If we don’t get free,

252
00:11:23,784 --> 00:11:26,220
the magnetic force
will just continue to intensify.

253
00:11:26,253 --> 00:11:28,956
Should we keep running
until we’re out of range?

254
00:11:28,989 --> 00:11:30,691
That might be our best bet.

255
00:11:30,724 --> 00:11:33,594
Joseph: No way. We might be able
to get away from her powers

256
00:11:33,627 --> 00:11:34,728
for a short amount of time,

257
00:11:34,761 --> 00:11:36,296
but the stand
would still prevail.

258
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:38,065
I’ve run away
from fights before,

259
00:11:38,098 --> 00:11:39,366
but i’ve only done so

260
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:41,868
when running was part
of the overall strategy.

261
00:11:41,902 --> 00:11:43,370
No matter
how hopeless things look,

262
00:11:43,403 --> 00:11:45,939
Joseph joestar
never throws in the towel.

263
00:11:45,973 --> 00:11:48,976
The real showdown begins now!

264
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:50,010
Avdol: Hmm?

265
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:54,815
Joseph: I’ve drawn
a map of the town.

266
00:11:54,848 --> 00:11:58,752
Here’s our current position, and
here’s where the woman’s going.

267
00:11:58,785 --> 00:12:01,755
As long as she continues moving
down this road,

268
00:12:01,788 --> 00:12:04,190
she’ll eventually loop around
and head back this way.

269
00:12:04,224 --> 00:12:06,026
We’ll split up, and...

270
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:08,662
Right here is where
we’ll catch that witch.

271
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:10,997
It doesn’t matter
if she’s a woman or not.

272
00:12:11,031 --> 00:12:15,202
When we catch her, she’s getting
a taste of my boot!

273
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:16,203
Let’s get going!

274
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:17,704
Man: Check it out.

275
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:20,040
Man #2: Oh, yeah.
Someone’s cut the rails.

276
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:22,309
Avdol: Good.
The locals are here.

277
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:24,711
I’m sure one of them
will have the foresight

278
00:12:24,745 --> 00:12:26,747
to notify the authorities
about the tracks

279
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:28,248
before the next train arrives.

280
00:12:28,282 --> 00:12:30,251
Joseph: Come on!

281
00:12:30,284 --> 00:12:33,888
( Iggy yawns )

282
00:12:34,922 --> 00:12:37,324
( Men panting )

283
00:12:37,357 --> 00:12:38,325
Polnareff: Huh?

284
00:12:38,358 --> 00:12:40,126
Something is definitely up.

285
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:42,396
Man: Hey! Did you hear
someone cut the rail line?!

286
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:44,164
Man #2: What about
all the trains?

287
00:12:44,198 --> 00:12:46,901
Man #1: Luckily they’ve stopped
running, at least for now.

288
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:49,069
Polnareff: Someone actually cut
the rail line?

289
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:51,671
People nowadays sure
are sick, don’t you think?

290
00:12:51,705 --> 00:12:55,008
Who in their right mind
would do something so terrible?

291
00:12:55,042 --> 00:12:56,377
Major douche canoe.

292
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:59,179
( Sighs ) Jotaro,
you wanna know what I think?

293
00:12:59,213 --> 00:13:01,749
Rotten people always get
what’s coming to ’em.

294
00:13:01,782 --> 00:13:04,852
You Mark my words.
They’ll get theirs.

295
00:13:04,885 --> 00:13:07,054
( Jotaro sighs )

296
00:13:07,087 --> 00:13:09,089
♪

297
00:13:15,963 --> 00:13:18,332
♪

298
00:13:20,734 --> 00:13:23,170
Man: I saved three months’
salary, all for this.

299
00:13:23,203 --> 00:13:24,705
Will you marry me?

300
00:13:24,738 --> 00:13:25,772
Woman: Oh, my!

301
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:26,774
- ( Metal humming )
- ( Clank )

302
00:13:26,807 --> 00:13:28,075
- Both: Huh?
- Man: What the?

303
00:13:28,108 --> 00:13:29,743
Wait! Where did the--

304
00:13:29,776 --> 00:13:30,777
woman: The ring!

305
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:41,054
Mariah: Those morons
are getting closer to me,

306
00:13:41,088 --> 00:13:43,424
but at this rate,
they’ll never catch me.

307
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:45,459
( Joseph grunts )

308
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:46,460
( Avdol grunts )

309
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:48,829
♪

310
00:13:48,862 --> 00:13:52,232
Cyclist: Huh? ( Yelling )

311
00:13:57,371 --> 00:13:59,740
( Joseph grunting )

312
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:10,984
Shopkeeper:
Almost there. Almost there.

313
00:14:11,018 --> 00:14:12,286
Man: Hmm?

314
00:14:12,319 --> 00:14:14,822
( Grunting )

315
00:14:17,424 --> 00:14:18,992
( Yells )

316
00:14:20,828 --> 00:14:24,265
( Joseph grunting )

317
00:14:34,975 --> 00:14:37,244
( Mariah laughs )

318
00:14:37,277 --> 00:14:40,447
I must say you’re looking
a little weighted down.

319
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,249
But don’t worry.
The wild-goose chase ends here.

320
00:14:43,283 --> 00:14:45,252
( Joseph groans )

321
00:14:45,285 --> 00:14:48,388
Interestingly enough,
it would seem that the two of us

322
00:14:48,422 --> 00:14:50,958
are more familiar with this town
than you are.

323
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:52,893
You should take a look
behind you.

324
00:14:52,926 --> 00:14:55,028
( Mariah gasps )

325
00:14:55,062 --> 00:14:56,830
Avdol: You’re now
caught between us,

326
00:14:56,864 --> 00:14:58,933
and there’s nowhere
for you to run.

327
00:14:58,966 --> 00:15:01,402
It may have
taken a while to get here,

328
00:15:01,435 --> 00:15:03,037
but the tables have turned.

329
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:05,072
♪

330
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:11,245
( Mariah laughing )

331
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:13,247
( Joseph growls )

332
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,249
( Avdol grunts ) Hmm?

333
00:15:15,282 --> 00:15:17,851
( Metal humming )

334
00:15:17,885 --> 00:15:20,054
Mariah: So you think
I have nowhere to go?

335
00:15:20,087 --> 00:15:22,356
You boys truly haven’t
realized it yet, have you?

336
00:15:22,389 --> 00:15:24,892
You only thought
you were hunting me,

337
00:15:24,925 --> 00:15:28,028
when really I was luring you
here the entire time!

338
00:15:28,061 --> 00:15:29,429
Look up, idiots!

339
00:15:30,464 --> 00:15:31,865
Both: Huh?

340
00:15:31,899 --> 00:15:33,901
♪

341
00:15:33,934 --> 00:15:35,369
Joseph: High-voltage
power lines!

342
00:15:35,402 --> 00:15:37,371
Avdol: Oh, no!
The power lines are--

343
00:15:37,404 --> 00:15:39,406
( Mariah laughs )
That’s right.

344
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:41,875
Power lines
are extremely magnetic!

345
00:15:41,909 --> 00:15:44,078
( Joseph groaning )

346
00:15:46,914 --> 00:15:50,284
Mariah: I’m afraid you’re
going to fry this time, joestar!

347
00:15:50,317 --> 00:15:52,820
Avdol: Magician’s red!

348
00:15:52,853 --> 00:15:54,221
( Magician’s red squawks )

349
00:15:54,254 --> 00:15:55,822
( Joseph groans )

350
00:15:55,856 --> 00:15:57,458
Hermit purple!

351
00:15:57,491 --> 00:15:59,460
( Groans )

352
00:15:59,493 --> 00:16:02,830
Mariah: Avdol might be able
to defend himself for now

353
00:16:02,863 --> 00:16:04,798
with his flames, but not you.

354
00:16:04,832 --> 00:16:06,167
Time to die, joestar.

355
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:09,003
My stand, the goddess bast
is the perfect trap,

356
00:16:09,036 --> 00:16:12,239
and it’s also far more powerful
than your hermit purple!

357
00:16:13,373 --> 00:16:15,108
Hope you’ve said your prayers,

358
00:16:15,142 --> 00:16:16,844
because it’s time to die!

359
00:16:16,877 --> 00:16:18,979
( Joseph groaning )

360
00:16:25,285 --> 00:16:26,520
Avdol: Vile woman.

361
00:16:26,553 --> 00:16:29,056
My flames will burn you
and your evil alive!

362
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:30,490
- ( Metal humming )
- ( Mariah chuckles )

363
00:16:30,524 --> 00:16:32,393
( Avdol gasps )

364
00:16:32,426 --> 00:16:35,062
( Groaning )

365
00:16:35,095 --> 00:16:38,532
My entire body is being pulled
in another direction!

366
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:40,400
I--i can’t resist!

367
00:16:47,941 --> 00:16:49,309
( Groans )

368
00:16:50,911 --> 00:16:52,212
My flames should be
strong enough

369
00:16:52,246 --> 00:16:53,948
to melt the steel
without a problem,

370
00:16:53,981 --> 00:16:55,950
but I can’t defend myself
from every attack,

371
00:16:55,983 --> 00:16:59,553
and this weight is crushing me!

372
00:16:59,586 --> 00:17:01,822
( Joseph groaning )

373
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:04,257
( Yelling )

374
00:17:05,425 --> 00:17:07,961
I can’t hold it any longer!

375
00:17:07,995 --> 00:17:11,599
Mariah: Joseph joestar, since
you’re going to die anyway,

376
00:17:11,632 --> 00:17:15,536
I can confess that I find you
to be quite a catch.

377
00:17:15,569 --> 00:17:19,073
It’s true that I only knew you
for a short time,

378
00:17:19,106 --> 00:17:21,141
but you were
so clever and hilarious,

379
00:17:21,175 --> 00:17:22,877
not to mention your experience

380
00:17:22,910 --> 00:17:26,013
would make younger men
green with envy,

381
00:17:26,046 --> 00:17:27,514
plus you’re very handsome.

382
00:17:27,548 --> 00:17:30,885
I know that you and I
are decades apart,

383
00:17:30,918 --> 00:17:33,053
but if i’m being
honest with myself,

384
00:17:33,086 --> 00:17:36,323
you would have made
a splendid lover. ( Chuckles )

385
00:17:36,356 --> 00:17:39,526
Joseph: Well, if that’s how
you truly feel about me,

386
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:42,029
then what do you say
you give me a hand?

387
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:43,564
Mariah: Hmm.

388
00:17:43,597 --> 00:17:46,200
Joseph: I’ve seen the light
and realize that your stand

389
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:49,002
is way more powerful
than mine could ever hope to be!

390
00:17:49,036 --> 00:17:51,105
I can’t hold it anymore!

391
00:17:51,138 --> 00:17:52,606
Please! I’m begging you!

392
00:17:52,639 --> 00:17:55,041
You have to turn off
the magnetism!

393
00:17:55,075 --> 00:17:57,177
Well, I suppose I could...

394
00:17:57,211 --> 00:17:59,180
( Joseph groaning )

395
00:17:59,213 --> 00:18:01,415
Mariah: But, no,
I don’t think I will.

396
00:18:01,448 --> 00:18:03,550
While you are
exceptionally handsome,

397
00:18:03,584 --> 00:18:05,920
you’re nowhere near
as good-looking as lord dio.

398
00:18:05,953 --> 00:18:08,389
Joseph: So you’re
saying that you refuse

399
00:18:08,422 --> 00:18:10,124
to turn off the power
no matter what?

400
00:18:10,157 --> 00:18:11,358
Mariah: Exactly right.

401
00:18:11,391 --> 00:18:13,493
Now don’t you have
some dying to do?

402
00:18:13,527 --> 00:18:15,529
Joseph: Even though
i’m groveling to you?

403
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:18,198
Mariah: I won’t say it again,
you idiot.

404
00:18:18,232 --> 00:18:20,668
Joseph: If that’s
how you’re going to be,

405
00:18:20,701 --> 00:18:22,570
then it’s your loss, young lady.

406
00:18:22,603 --> 00:18:23,571
Mariah: What?!

407
00:18:23,604 --> 00:18:26,574
♪

408
00:18:26,607 --> 00:18:28,375
Mariah: Shit! Shit!

409
00:18:28,408 --> 00:18:30,243
- ( Gasps )
- ( Avdol yells )

410
00:18:32,145 --> 00:18:33,446
( Bones cracking )

411
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,115
( Mariah gags )

412
00:18:35,148 --> 00:18:37,117
Joseph: Weren’t you
listening to us earlier?

413
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:39,319
You’ve been caught
between us the whole time.

414
00:18:39,353 --> 00:18:41,488
Magnets are attracted
to each other, you know.

415
00:18:41,522 --> 00:18:44,258
It’s too late
to do anything about it now,

416
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,627
but getting between us
was your biggest blunder.

417
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:49,396
Avdol: There’s no way
she can hear you, Mr. Joestar.

418
00:18:49,429 --> 00:18:51,364
She’s already
lost consciousness.

419
00:18:51,398 --> 00:18:53,634
All the metal and magnetic force
has crushed her,

420
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:55,302
and it’s very likely

421
00:18:55,335 --> 00:18:58,038
that she’s broken more than
a few bones in the process.

422
00:18:58,071 --> 00:18:59,072
( Squish )

423
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:02,309
( Metal clattering )

424
00:19:06,346 --> 00:19:07,447
Joseph: Hmm.

425
00:19:07,481 --> 00:19:10,317
( Both grunting )

426
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:12,319
( Crowd gasps )

427
00:19:12,352 --> 00:19:14,054
Avdol: Hmm.

428
00:19:15,355 --> 00:19:17,424
Joseph: Hmm.

429
00:19:17,457 --> 00:19:19,159
All right,

430
00:19:19,193 --> 00:19:22,296
why don’t we get that breakfast
we were talking about?

431
00:19:22,329 --> 00:19:24,998
Avdol: Yes, a wonderful idea.

432
00:19:25,032 --> 00:19:27,501
All this running around
has made me rather hungry.

433
00:19:27,534 --> 00:19:29,569
Joseph: Is it really
only 9 A.M.?

434
00:19:29,603 --> 00:19:32,106
Mariah: Damn,
you pieces of shit--

435
00:19:32,139 --> 00:19:33,240
( sighs )

436
00:19:33,273 --> 00:19:35,275
( Typewriter clacking )

437
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:43,283
Polnareff: Those two
are taking forever!

438
00:19:43,317 --> 00:19:45,052
As long as they’ve
been in there,

439
00:19:45,085 --> 00:19:46,620
you’d think they were
putting on makeup

440
00:19:46,653 --> 00:19:48,021
and dressing for a gala.

441
00:19:48,055 --> 00:19:49,123
( Iggy growls )

442
00:19:49,156 --> 00:19:51,492
Jotaro: And it’s almost 9 A.M.

443
00:19:51,525 --> 00:19:52,626
( Sighs )

444
00:19:52,659 --> 00:19:54,461
Polnareff: Hmm.

445
00:19:54,495 --> 00:19:57,765
Jotaro: They may have run into
an enemy on the way here.

446
00:19:57,798 --> 00:20:00,668
Polnareff: You think we should
see where they ran off to?

447
00:20:00,701 --> 00:20:03,370
Jotaro: I guess.
Ah, good grief.

448
00:20:03,403 --> 00:20:05,405
Polnareff:
It’s time to go, iggy.

449
00:20:05,439 --> 00:20:06,407
( Iggy groans )

450
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,741
( Barks )

451
00:20:07,774 --> 00:20:10,110
Polnareff: Yeah, yeah,
I know you’re hungry.

452
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:12,412
You’re not the only one,
believe me.

453
00:20:12,446 --> 00:20:13,681
( Iggy groans )

454
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,519
Man: Hmm.

455
00:20:18,552 --> 00:20:20,354
♪

456
00:20:20,387 --> 00:20:22,856
Josef and avdol
are in the middle

457
00:20:22,890 --> 00:20:26,227
of doing battle with Mariah,
so I, alessi,

458
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:30,464
shall take on the great honor
of killing jotaro and polnareff.

459
00:20:30,497 --> 00:20:32,499
( Laughing )

460
00:20:38,805 --> 00:20:40,807
♪

